In CardboardStudio, The "Publisher Links" are just WebServers. This means the script is technically just giving the API Key, Part holding table, 
Instance holding table, And all of the properties of the instances. This allows for external applications to translate entire JSON-Encoded tables
containing Roblox game data, However they want. So to seperate Publisher from Non-Publisher,
Every external application via WebServer that mainly utilizes ported CardboardStudio data, Must have the WebServer's URL and Name placed in this list.

Because there are none right now, This is only an Example.

(Name): (your webserver)
Description: Mango Port ports mango.
